id: pm-itb0
title: Calendar --include scheduled alias missing (calendar summary uses 'scheduled' but filter requires 'events')
description: "The pm calendar summary field is named 'scheduled: N' for event-kind entries, but the --include filter only accepts 'events', not 'scheduled'. Agents reading the summary output and trying --include scheduled get exit 2. Fixed by adding 'scheduled' as an accepted alias for 'events' in parseIncludeSources."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agents,calendar,terminology,ux
created_at: "2026-05-01T18:58:56.749Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-01T19:29:07.567Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-3fti
severity: medium
resolution: Added 'scheduled' as alias for 'events' in parseIncludeSources in calendar.ts. Updated error message to include the alias.
expected_result: "Expected closure outcome: Fixed: parseIncludeSources in calendar.ts now accepts 'scheduled' as alias for 'events'. Verified: pm cal --include scheduled works."
actual_result: "Actual closure outcome: Fixed: parseIncludeSources in calendar.ts now accepts 'scheduled' as alias for 'events'. Verified: pm cal --include scheduled works."
close_reason: "Fixed: parseIncludeSources in calendar.ts now accepts 'scheduled' as alias for 'events'. Verified: pm cal --include scheduled works."
